      "name": "Flower Illustration",
      "artisticStyle": "Botanical Illustration",
      "medium": "Digital Illustration",
      "creationDate": "2025",
      "insight": "\"BEING AS IT IS\" — Interactive Media Art Series\nLaunched in 2025, this series marks the artist's transition from static generative imagery toward interactive media — a shift driven by the recognition that stillness alone could no longer fully express the project's core idea.\nRooted in Schopenhauer's concept of pure contemplation from The World as Will and Representation, the work explores a simple but profound truth: plants and animals exist without regret for the past or anxiety about the future. They do not seek to justify their presence — they simply are. Building on the generative art practice developed between 2021 and 2023, the artist now turns to AI and interactive media to give that presence motion, response, and breath.\nIn this series, audiences are invited to interact with nature rendered on screen. In doing so, the act of observing the natural world becomes something more — a moment of turning inward, and becoming aware of one's own existence in the present.\n",
      "url": "",
      "showThumbnailInGallery": false
    },
