      "name": "Animated Nature Series",
      "artisticStyle": "Animation / Nature Art",
      "medium": "Digital Animation",
      "creationDate": "2025",
      "insight": "A natural extension of the artist's long-running exploration of plants and animals in harmony, this series revisits familiar subjects — creatures nestled within botanical forms, living quietly inside flowerpots — and gives them something new: movement.\nWith the arrival of AI-driven tools, the artist began experimenting with animating the illustrated worlds previously confined to static images. The same compositions that once existed as still drawings now breathe, shift, and respond — leaves tremble, animals stir, and the boundary between image and living thing becomes gently blurred. This series represents an early and intentional experiment, a test of how motion can deepen the work's central question: what does it look and feel like to simply exist, as nature does, in the present moment?\nRather than a finished body of work, these pieces are offered as an honest record of exploration — the artist's first steps into the expanding territory where hand-drawn sensibility meets the generative possibilities of AI media.",
      "url": "",
      "showThumbnailInGallery": false
