      "name": "Exchanging my talents for traveling in Ireland.",
      "artisticStyle": "Travel Illustration / Documentary Art",
      "medium": "Mixed Media (Digital and Traditional)",
      "creationDate": "2017",
      "insight": "DRAWING IRELAND PROJECT\nWhat began as a simple question — \"Can I exchange my artistic talents for accommodations while traveling Ireland?\" — grew into one of the most meaningful journeys of my life.\nInspired by HelpX, a platform connecting budget travelers with hosts in need of practical help, I reimagined the concept through an artistic lens. Rather than offering manual labor, I proposed something more personal: my drawings. To bring the idea to life, I built a dedicated website where hosts could learn about the project and apply to participate.\nThe response led me to three remarkable hosts across Ireland. I spent time at Gallic Kitchen, a beloved Irish restaurant in Abbeyleix; Fheoirfurniture, an intimate furniture design studio; and Camphill Grangemockler, a volunteer community dedicated to people with special needs. In each place, I created artwork in exchange for a roof, a meal, and the warmth of genuine human connection.\nWhat I brought home was more than a portfolio — it was a collection of nostalgic, irreplaceable memories shaped by the people who opened their doors to me.",
      "url": "https://www.behance.net/gallery/112683413/Exchanging-my-talents-for-traveling-in-Ireland",
      "showThumbnailInGallery": false
    },
